caption: Good local fresh and tasty fast food place.  The service is somewhat lazy and dismissive.  Update: Service has improved.

Really delicious choices for vegans, vegetarians and omnivores. I love the "sweet heat" burger and they have great salads. I appreciate the attention to community and environmental awareness--they have descriptions of where their food comes from, and pictures of farmers, on the walls. Also, good prices for specialty Brooklyn food.
This place is amazing.  Great food, great staff, great atmosphere.
The food is regularly fresh and tasty, cashiers hands out excellent service. I loved how neat it is and atmosphere. Will come back again.
Got the chicken and avocado sandwich with vegetables instead of the bun. Healthy, filling, and tasty.

I would give this place 2.5 stars. Tasty burger and fries, however, very pricey for the very small portions! Cashier seemed very confused when I tried to simply order a cheese burger, she said "so you don't want meat?", I said "umm, a burger with cheese.", she repeated her question. I then said can I get the classic with no lettuce, no tomato, red onion, relish, or secret sauce but just have cheese on it (yes, just meat, cheese & bun - not complicated). She made a face as if I was requesting something odd. If you work in food, you must learn to not sneer at customers request.

Foods are fresh and super healthy. I enjoyed my meal, however I would not come back as its TOO healthy for my liking. There are seating outside and in the front of the store. You order after the steps. A small variety of everything. A couple salad choices, burger choices, chicken choices, and smoothie. At the back of the store, there is the restroom and an utensil station. The utensil station is super cute, clean and organized. Their ketchup DOES NOT have fructose corn syrup. Organic AF. Ordered a Chicken Caser salad, with tax littler under $12.00. Got my food relatively fast. Chicken was dry. Croutons which I believe are whole wheat. B. Good offer kids menu, which I believe to be super worth it, if you are trying something new or you would like a snack. Kids menu comes with a drink, applesauce, fries, and carrots. Plates and bowls comes in biodegradable materials. Recommend: if you're scared of trying something new, try the kids menu. Kids menu comes with a variety of chooses.

This place has never let me down. I always go for the Southwestern chicken salad with an added egg. It's always fresh and tastes really good, compared to nearby Monty Qs Salad. The only reason why I didn't give it a 5 star is because it is a bit more pricier than Monty Qs. Monty Qs also has a salad card (think of it like frequent customer care) that gives you a free salad (well upto $10 value) after buying 10 salads. Burgers at b.good are also really delicious and not as greasy as nearby eateries.

The restaurant is a clean, well lit place! When you walk through the door, you pass a seating area and then walk down a few stairs to get to the main seating area and counter. I arrived around 6 PM on a Tuesday evening and it was pretty much empty. More patrons rolled in around 6:30 PM. The menu was simple but still had enough variety in its options. I ordered the the Maple Bacon burger, becasue it's a seasonal item with a side order of sweet potato fries. The burger was a fair size and was very tasty. I enjoyed the spicy slaw that came on the burger! The fries were not greasy, for me, had the right amount of salt. Even though I had a burger, I would like to visit here again to try another menu item.

A great place to eat....the atmosphere is warm and the staff is very courteous . I love their eggplant meatballs, and their burgers and sweet potatoes are unbelievable... I would definitely  recommend this place if you are looking for a friendly place that also accommodate kids. I give 👍.l giveB.GOOD a rating of 10.

I wish I could tell you the gentleman's name, but he was a young man that made my veggie sandwich. I was a bit hesitant to tell him that I wanted hotter fries because I didn't want to be one of those complaining customers, but without attitude, he offered me a new bag with a smile! From the time I entered the store till I left, all of the employees showed me kindness and respect so shout out to the manager!!! The food was decent, I love the menue options since it offer not only burgers, but smoothies and salads! The point is, althought it wasn't my favorite veggie burger, I would highly recommended B.GOOD to all because of the service and the fact they will make it to your liking if you don't like it. Try it! I got the veggie burger, you may enjoy something else!!😏

Food was mediocre.  Feels a bit overpriced considering the food.  I got the beef el guapo over a bed of veggies and the paty  was very dry, didn't have much of any flavor. The veggies (carrots, broccoli, zucchini, kale) were salted, but again, there wasn't much any flavor going on there. I work around the corner from B good ! As a vegetarian, I love the veggie burger and salad bowl options that they have along with the sweet potato fries. I have tried all the bowls since most of them are vegetarian options. However, I went for lunch last week and I ordered power bow without egg and the portion was so small. I didn’t understand how the employee that made the bowl didn’t realize that the portion was so small and the bowl was not even half full. I know their portion sizes are perfect but last week I was not pleased to pay $11 and change for a small portion bowl that did not fill me up. Hopefully they are mindful the next time they are giving half full bowl to someone for lunch .

B. Good serves up healthy and tasty meals that are fresh and true to the original flavors. My favorites are the bowls, which are deceptively large, full of roasted veggies, grains, and greens, but very lightly dressed. The burgers are also very good and I love the options for turkey or veggie burgers. I'm a fan of the kids menus.

We dropped in for a quick bite at lunchtime on a slow Sunday. We were the only customers in the place yet the server gave us extreme attitude when we walked in. She grunted at us when we politely asked for a menu, she looked sullen when we asked to order food and she sneered at us that we weren't allowed to order from the kids' menu (the options for vegetarians are very poor indeed so I didn't have a lot of choice - what difference does it make to her what we eat?). Both members of staff were standing around doing nothing when we walked in, yet we were treated as if we were interrupting them. Very poor menu, very rude staff. We left without purchasing anything and won't be going back.

B.good is fine. It’s a healthier twist on junky fast food and they do a good job on some of their food items. But it is kind of confusing because they will have a pure healthy quinoa salad as well as a local organic burger with buttery white bread. It’s as if some stuff is super healthy (not really a twist on any fast food) and other stuff is a nice twist like the burger. However even though the burger is a good offering, it didn’t taste very good and the burger was much smaller than the bun. The quinoa salad was surprisingly better and a much bigger portion.

Signed up for the app through instagram and got a free meal! It was great! Everything was freshly made. Vegan and Vegetarian options. Lots of space and the workers are nice! They have affordable prices. Smoothies are good! Overall a good environment to eat in.

When I stumbled across this restaurant for the first time it was great! At the moment it was quiet so ordering and receiving the food was nice and easy. The chicken sandwich I got was good and presented very well.  However the next time that I visited it wasn’t so quiet, in fact the place was very busy.  I ordered two burgers and two shakes for my girlfriend and I (which was now her first time) at 12:10.  I did not receive my food until 12:56 and even notice that people who came after me got their food first. On top of the wait the order was slightly wrong and presented very sloppy, my bun was hard and my girlfriends was soggy. Keep in mind it looked as if they had a short handed staff, especially compared to the customers that they attract. My advice: It ultimately is a fine restaurant with good food and styling, as long as there is no line. If there is a line expect a long wait and rushed service.

I used to come to this spot almost weekly but stopped when my favorite staff members moves to other locations. So glad I returned and can't wait to eat my zucchini and eegplant bowl. Plus I'll be happy to try their shaved Brussels sprouts salad.

I recommend the salads and bowls, don't touch the burgers. Also the fries were burnt and soggy.

I just spent $18 on horrible food. The food was served at room temperature (at best). Nothing looked or tasted fresh. The food seemed a day or two old. I ordered the vegan burger, fries and a smoothie. The fries were old and tasted awful. The vegan burger was super crusty and extra crunchy (a crunchy burger? 😝🤔😫🙊) and extremely dry. There was a ridiculously  thick sliced tomato on the burger, along with the end of a pickle (really? The end of the pickle).The smoothie was pretty good, but not worth $7(especially being that they used caned ingredients instead natural fruit. The overall experience was atrocious to say the least. The staff wasn't very efficient. They forgot to serve my drink with my order and I had to ask the person making my smoothie to wash the disgusting blender before preparing my drink 😝. I wouldn't recommend this place to a stray hungry dog, let alone a human being. DON'T EAT HERE!!!! I went to the location in Brooklyn, on Montegue ST.
